21:23.559 --> 21:24.720
-Perfect natural.

21:27.400 --> 21:30.359
-I'm not that together.

21:30.400 --> 21:32.839
Next year, all my friends will
either be overseas of in the

21:32.880 --> 21:37.200
company, and I'll be lonely.

21:37.240 --> 21:38.400
-Lonely sucks.

22:15.599 --> 22:17.519
NARRATOR: I'm going to give up
the idea of traveling light is

22:17.559 --> 22:20.160
an impossible concept.

22:20.200 --> 22:21.680
It's cumulative.

22:21.720 --> 22:25.559
Every experience we have, every
person we meet, they

22:25.599 --> 22:28.599
make up the story of
you like a journal.

22:28.640 --> 22:29.799
-Saying goodbye?

22:31.839 --> 22:33.799
-That was the plan.

22:46.640 --> 22:48.160
NARRATOR: I guess it's only when
you go to throw something

22:48.200 --> 22:50.799
out you realize how
essential it is.

23:04.839 --> 23:05.839
TARA (VOICEMAIL):
Hey, it's Tara.

23:05.880 --> 23:07.200
Sorry I can't get to you.

23:07.240 --> 23:09.200
-I did bad, and I get it.

23:09.240 --> 23:11.680
But you have to come see this.

23:11.720 --> 23:14.279
It's like you in a place.

23:14.319 --> 23:15.480
It's-- it's beautiful.

23:21.200 --> 23:23.680
NARRATOR: Like it or not, there
are some things that--

23:23.720 --> 23:24.839
[knocking]

23:24.880 --> 23:28.240
NARRATOR: --are permanently
inscribed that

23:28.279 --> 23:29.440
you're stuck with.

23:31.680 --> 23:33.559
-Can I talk to you later?

23:33.599 --> 23:34.599
Go away, Christian.

23:34.640 --> 23:35.599
-Wait, what happened?

23:35.640 --> 23:38.440
You OK?

23:38.480 --> 23:41.759
-No, I'm just sick of it.

23:41.799 --> 23:45.240
I keep thinking, when is
this going to stop?

23:45.279 --> 23:48.200
Because I want so much
to be rid of you.

23:48.240 --> 23:50.279
It's all I could think about
during that ceremony.

23:52.880 --> 23:54.240
-Did it work?

